  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      Silverpeas 6 is out this month and it is distributed in several ways.
    </p>
    <section name="Try Silverpeas">
      <p>
        <img src="../images/logos/logo_izPack.png" alt="izpack" style="padding-right:10px;float:left;position:relative;"/>
        <br/>We provide an easy way to try Silverpeas 6 using
        <a href="http://izpack.org/">Izpack</a> with a pre-configured Wildfly application server and an H2 Database.</p>
      <p>
        You can find how to get in <a href="izpack.html">our dedicated page</a> how to get and use our installer.
      </p>
    </section>
    <section name="Install in production">
      <p>
        You whish to keep control on the installation process or to you whish to install Silverpeas in one of your production-ready servers running either with
        a Unix system or with MS-Windows, then please consult the instructions on <a href="installationV6.html">how to install our stable version of Silverpeas 6</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
    <section name="Ready for the Cloud">
      <p>
        <img src="../images/logos/logo_docker.png" alt="docker" style="padding-right:10px;float:left;position:relative;"/>
        <br/>Silverpeas 6 is also available as a Docker image in the Official image library in the Docker Hub. You will find
        information about the use of this image in our <a href="https://hub.docker.com/_/silverpeas/">official DockerHub repository</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
    <section name="Document Online Edition">
      <p>Silverpeas provides the users a way to edit the documents in Silverpeas by using their favorite Office Suite. This feature
      requires an external program to install on the user host. You will find more information about the online edition of documents
      in the <a href="webdav.html">dedicated page</a>.</p>
    </section>
    <section name="Problems">
      <p>If you encounter a problem during installation or if you have any question, you can post them on the <a href="http://groups.google.com/group/silverpeas-users" >users mailing-list</a></p>
    </section>
  </body>
